[15.573956, "o", "\r\nQ: can you trust experts and institutions    [backend=bm25, vault=sample_vault]\r\n"]
[15.574332, "o", "\r\n[1] Trust and expertise  ›  Division of epistemic labor — \"who do you trust?\"   (score 6.840)\r\n    file: sample_vault/Trust and expertise.md\r\n"]
[15.574364, "o", "    Core note behind the recurring point: a complex society runs on **trusting third parties** because no one can independently verify everything. The failure mode of new media is not \"question experts\" — it's replacing verifiable institutions with un-auditable personalities.\r\n    citations (from this note):\r\n      • https://www.jstor.org/stable/2026523\r\n      • https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2024/06/24/public-trust-in-government-1958-2024/\r\n      • Hardwig, J. (1985)\r\n"]
[15.57854, "o", "\r\n"]
[17.780179, "o", "\u001b[2m# Point --vault at an export of the real vault and it runs unchanged.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[20.382785, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[32mThe homework you already did — retrievable, and cited, in one query.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
